    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, STANDARD AND TILT - 2000, 3000, 4000, 8000 - UNIVERSAL JOINTS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>UNIVERSAL JOINTS</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>To service steering column universal joints, it is first necessary to remove the steering column from
                the vehicle.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Use extreme care not to damage bearing surfaces.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
            <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the universal joint in a vise as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501306">Figure 6</hotlnk>. Remove the snap rings retaining the bearings in the
                    yoke.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0501306" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0501306" filename="../figg05/G0501306.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6. Place Universal Joint in Vise</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. BEARING</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. YOKE</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. SPIDER</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. SNAP RING</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the shaft assembly in a vise as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501307">Figure 7</hotlnk>. Tap the yoke with a soft hammer beside the bearing that
                    is being removed. The bearing should come out. If the bearing does not come out, place the bearing
                    in a vise. Use copper jaw covers on vise. Tap the yoke away from the bearing as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501308">Figure 8</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0501307" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0501307" filename="../figg05/G0501307.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7. Place Shaft Assembly in Vise</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. BEARING</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. YOKE</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f0501308" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0501308" filename="../figg05/G0501308.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8. Tap Yoke Away From Bearing</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. YOKE</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. BEARING</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the spider after the bearings have been removed.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
